<dl id="n11126h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11126h">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11126h"> 126(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Le Sage / Duclos (Bretons)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Notice</b> Si jamais &eacute;crivain subit et garda l&apos;empreinte de son terroir, c&apos;est bien Chateaubriand. On l&apos;a contest&eacute;. On a oppos&eacute; &agrave; son cas celui de <mark>Le Sage et de Duclos, deux autres Bretons</mark> qui ne lui ressemblent gu&egrave;re, assure-t-on. Ils lui ressemblent plus qu&apos;on ne croit. Ce sont des ind&eacute;pendants comme lui. <br><font color="green">[If ever a writer has received and retained the imprint of his native soil, Chateaubriand is such a one. This has been contested. His case has been set against those of Le Sage and Duclos, both Bretons who hardly resembled him, they say. Yet they resemble him more than one might think. They are independent minds, as he is.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) I, 5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
